Her reporting at the station spans daily assignments, special reports, breaking news and a documentary. Vicki earned a 2020 Regional Edward R. Murrow award for the hourlong news documentary “Return to Paradise”, following four resilient families for a year after the Camp Fire -- the deadliest wildfire in California history. The documentary premiered in the town of Paradise and was followed by a Q&A with the families. In 2019, she earned a regional Emmy award for the half-hour special “Hope, Humanity & Housing”, which looked at the health disparities of affordable housing and those experiencing homelessness. Vicki put together the news special as a California Fellow with USC Annenberg’s Center for Health Journalism. That same year, her reporting on the Thousand Oaks mass shooting in Southern California was part of a 2019 regional Emmy award for KCRA 3’s 4 p.m. newscast. In 2018, her reporting on the Oroville Dam spillway crisis, Santa Rosa wildfire, Las Vegas mass shooting and the transgender youth series, “Now I Am Me”, was part of KCRA 3’s National Edward R. Murrow award for News Excellence. That same year, her digital reporting on Oroville Dam and Santa Rosa’s wildfire was part of KCRA 3’s regional Edward R. Murrow award for Innovation. Prior to KCRA 3, Vicki worked at KSNV-TV in Las Vegas as a reporter, KFXV-TV in the Rio Grande Valley, Texas, as an anchor/producer, got her professional start in journalism at KABC-TV in Los Angeles as an online news producer and interned at KGO-TV in San Francisco while attending UC Berkeley. Born in Los Angeles, Vicki is a California native and proud of her roots. Her abuelos are from Guadalajara, her grandmother from Kobe, Japan, and her English grandfather was born and raised in Kolkata (Calcutta), India. Adding to geography, her parents met in Hawaii! She was raised in Eagle Rock and graduated from Eagle Rock High. However, she is tremendously happy to call Sacramento home with her husband and cats! You can find Vicki at the farmer’s market, floating down the American River, on the Jedediah Smith bike trail or bouncing around local restaurants. Outside of town, Vicki is usually exploring the endless trails, lakes and rivers Northern California has to offer. Follow Vicki on social to see what she’s up to next!
